WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:20.220 --> 00:01:24.550
KAMOGAWA Boxing Gym

3
00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:36.460
All right. that's enough.

4
00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:39.230
Thank you. sir!

5
00:01:39.310 --> 00:01:40.570
Right.

6
00:01:41.880 --> 00:01:45.310
A bit of inactivity hasn't
dulled his power blow.

7
00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:49.480
So. what shall we do about
the A-Class Tournament?

8
00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:52.080
His punches haven't weakened...

9
00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:54.590
but he hasn't done
nearly enough sparring.

10
00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:56.450
I'm sure his match sense
has dulled down...

11
00:01:56.520 --> 00:01:58.790
and we haven't come up with
a game plan to fight Saeki.

12
00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:00.620
Ow...

13
00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:02.180
Are you all right. Chief?

14
00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:05.320
The kid hit me with nothing
but right body blows.

15
00:02:06.430 --> 00:02:07.590
Body blows?!

16
00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:09.200
Hey. kid.

17
00:02:09.270 --> 00:02:10.330
Yes?

18
00:02:11.570 --> 00:02:13.540
Are you all right. Chief?

19
00:02:13.610 --> 00:02:17.600
Little fool! I'm not wimpy enough
to be swayed by your punches.

20
00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:20.740
You used an awful lot of body blows.
so it got to me a little. you see.

21
00:02:20.810 --> 00:02:22.150
I'm sorry.

22
00:02:22.220 --> 00:02:24.150
Nah. that was a good way to hit.

23
00:02:24.220 --> 00:02:25.550
Do you think so?

24
00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:29.050
I imagined myself doing jabs
while moving clockwise...

25
00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:32.150
to intercept him
at that point like this.

26
00:02:32.230 --> 00:02:34.190
Who moves?

27
00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:36.390
Who moves clockwise?

28
00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:38.060
Uh. that's...

29
00:02:38.130 --> 00:02:40.930
So it's your best try at forming
a plan of attack against Saeki.

30
00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:44.660
Well. yes. But I definitely
need more practice. Um...

31
00:02:46.610 --> 00:02:50.570
In the meantime. you appear
to be making rapid preparations.

32
00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:53.610
Your plan of attack against Saeki
is right on target for now.

33
00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:55.170
However!

34
00:02:55.250 --> 00:02:58.910
If you're going to use it.
get in the ring intending to win!

35
00:02:58.990 --> 00:03:01.110
You're taking part in
the A-Class Tournament!

36
00:03:02.020 --> 00:03:03.180
Yes. sir!

37
00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:13.290
A-Class Tournament List of Boxers
Featherweight Entry No.4
Ippo MAKUNOUCHI (Kamogawa Gym)
Japan Featherweight Ranking No.5
Height 164 cm Weight 57 kg Reach 167 cm
Fight History
8 matches 8 wins (8 KO) no losses

38
00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:16.000
<i><font color="#ffff00">So. he came back.</font></i>

39
00:03:19.770 --> 00:03:21.710
NAKADAI Boxing Gym

40
00:03:23.010 --> 00:03:24.370
Good afternoon!

41
00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:31.540
So. they already started sparring.

42
00:03:34.620 --> 00:03:37.060
How's Saeki shaping up. Okita-kun?

43
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:40.250
He's fast.
Even Date-san can't catch him.

44
00:03:40.330 --> 00:03:43.230
I guess that's
the Speed Star for you.

45
00:03:48.700 --> 00:03:49.860
Good!

46
00:03:53.270 --> 00:03:54.400
Damn.

47
00:04:00.080 --> 00:04:03.210
Hmph! When all's said and done.
I failed to catch you.

48
00:04:03.280 --> 00:04:05.180
I was seriously trying to avoid that.

49
00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:08.190
Speed before style. huh?
You're my least favorite type.

50
00:04:08.920 --> 00:04:12.980
Least favorite? I'll take
those words as a compliment.

51
00:04:16.730 --> 00:04:18.090
He's a hateful little bastard.

52
00:04:19.430 --> 00:04:22.990
He won't use more than
60 to 70% of his full power.

53
00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:27.540
<i><font color="#ffff00">Would it have been more fun
to make him go all out?</font></i>

54
00:04:28.680 --> 00:04:30.270
<i><font color="#ffff00">Speed Star.</font></i>

55
00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:33.540
<i><font color="#ffff00">He isn't going to be
an opponent...</font></i>

56
00:04:33.610 --> 00:04:36.310
<i><font color="#ffff00">you can beat by
ordinary means. Makunouchi.</font></i>

57
00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:38.810
An opponent
that's hard to fight?

58
00:04:38.890 --> 00:04:41.790
Yes! Kimura-san. you...
I mean...

59
00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:45.150
To an outboxer. what kind of boxer
is most difficult to fight?

60
00:04:45.530 --> 00:04:46.920
Good question.

61
00:04:46.990 --> 00:04:49.890
The type of boxer who charges
forward relentlessly like you...

62
00:04:49.960 --> 00:04:51.260
is easy!

63
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:56.590
But the most difficult opponents are
those with better footwork than yourself.

64
00:04:56.670 --> 00:04:59.570
They always get ahead
one trick at a time...

65
00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:01.610
so you can't get your rhythm going.
you forget your pace.

66
00:05:01.670 --> 00:05:03.340
At any rate. it's hard going.

67
00:05:03.410 --> 00:05:06.340
Someone faster than yourself?

68
00:05:06.410 --> 00:05:08.070
I'm going to continue now.

69
00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:09.240
Oh. sure.

70
00:05:13.050 --> 00:05:16.850
<i><font color="#ffff00">That would mean that if
I can move faster than Saeki-san...</font></i>

71
00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:24.630
Is he trying to outbox?

72
00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:25.890
Sempai.

73
00:05:37.980 --> 00:05:39.440
Knock that off. you tone-deaf freak!

74
00:05:39.510 --> 00:05:41.880
You're screwing up my rhythm. too!

75
00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:43.180
I'm sorry!

76
00:05:43.250 --> 00:05:45.150
You can't do it! Give up!

77
00:05:46.950 --> 00:05:49.390
Toyo Athletic University

78
00:05:53.490 --> 00:05:54.520
Yo!

79
00:05:54.590 --> 00:05:56.530
Oh. Saeki-sempai!

80
00:05:56.600 --> 00:05:57.720
Good afternoon!

81
00:05:57.800 --> 00:06:01.670
Well. you guys are as lively as ever.
This brings back memories.

82
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.930
Saeki. you bastard!

83
00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.160
Thanks to you dropping out...

84
00:06:06.240 --> 00:06:08.730
we were slaughtered
in the university meet!

85
00:06:09.040 --> 00:06:10.910
You're looking well. Captain.

86
00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:13.440
So? What's it like being a pro?

87
00:06:15.010 --> 00:06:17.540
As I recall.
this white part of the glove...

88
00:06:17.620 --> 00:06:20.050
was your excuse for
quitting amateur boxing.

89
00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:24.450
You didn't like how hitting it scored
the same points as a knockdown.

90
00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:27.490
It's all well and good
to compete with techniques...

91
00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:28.990
but I found it lacked something.

92
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:31.460
Did you get what
you wanted in the pros?

93
00:06:34.300 --> 00:06:37.760
What can I say?
The professional guys sure are great!

94
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.700
They have murder in their fists.

95
00:06:40.770 --> 00:06:44.210
They strike at you risking their lives.
their souls in every shot.

96
00:06:45.140 --> 00:06:46.630
I dodge their punch
by the skin of my teeth...

97
00:06:46.710 --> 00:06:49.650
and in the next split-second.
I make my punch.

98
00:06:50.580 --> 00:06:53.920
That dog-eat-dog instant.
a mere hundredth of a second...

99
00:06:53.990 --> 00:06:57.980
is so great...
I can't get enough of it.

100
00:06:58.060 --> 00:07:02.360
So. you chose the path
with the most thrills.

101
00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:08.230
- Let me use that a second.

102
00:07:08.230 --> 00:07:09.100
- Let me use that a second.
- Uh. sure.

103
00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:13.970
You can't just leave this to strength.

104
00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:17.130
You need to use momentum.
In other words. your spring.

105
00:07:17.210 --> 00:07:18.580
Like this!

106
00:07:21.110 --> 00:07:22.100
Holy cow!

107
00:07:22.180 --> 00:07:26.480
The secret to Saeki's speed
is his extraordinary 'spring.'

108
00:07:27.950 --> 00:07:32.790
There can't be many who can keep up
with your speed. even in the pros.

109
00:07:32.860 --> 00:07:35.890
You probably can't get the thrill
you need if you can't get hit.

110
00:07:35.960 --> 00:07:39.590
I get my thrills. Especially
with my upcoming opponent.

111
00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:45.160
He's the man with the most
powerful fists in Japan Featherweight.

112
00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:51.270
<i><font color="#ffff00">I'm counting on you.
Makunouchi!</font></i>

113
00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:54.110
<i><font color="#ffff00">Give me that special thrill
you've been holding back!</font></i>

114
00:07:57.750 --> 00:08:00.950
A week till the tournament. huh?

115
00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:02.990
Did you formulate
some kind of plan?

116
00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:07.120
Nope. Petty tricks and
fast cramming never pay off.

117
00:08:07.190 --> 00:08:08.290
You got that right.

118
00:08:20.970 --> 00:08:24.600
Whoa. Ippo! You've gotten
pretty good at that. haven't you?

119
00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:30.670
Well. I've been studying sense
of rhythm nonstop the best I can.

120
00:08:31.420 --> 00:08:33.850
Maybe fast cramming has
its own measure of success?

121
00:08:33.920 --> 00:08:36.290
No. Hey. Ippo.

122
00:08:36.360 --> 00:08:39.660
Can you throw punches with a backbone
while maintaining that speed?

123
00:08:41.660 --> 00:08:44.390
I knew it. A professional
can see right through it.

124
00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:48.200
Once I put my hands into it.
my rhythm goes all over the place.

125
00:08:48.270 --> 00:08:51.500
If I can see that.
Saeki will see through it. too.

126
00:08:51.570 --> 00:08:54.130
I guess petty tricks
are no good after all.

127
00:08:54.210 --> 00:08:56.070
That was an exercise
in futility. Ippo!

128
00:08:57.780 --> 00:09:01.770
Sempai. I don't think
it's a futile exercise.

129
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:03.550
Yeah. me neither.

130
00:09:04.220 --> 00:09:07.520
If I can get closer to
Saeki-san's moves and rhythm...

131
00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:09.150
I might realize something.

132
00:09:10.190 --> 00:09:12.450
Do you mean.
to know thine enemy?

133
00:09:12.530 --> 00:09:14.360
Then let's try it again!

134
00:09:14.430 --> 00:09:16.220
I'll practice with you
as many times as it takes!

135
00:09:16.300 --> 00:09:17.590
Yeah.

136
00:09:18.460 --> 00:09:20.400
I'm going to punch you.

137
00:09:21.900 --> 00:09:24.670
It's difficult to do with you
staring me in the eye like that.

138
00:09:24.740 --> 00:09:28.400
I'm sorry.
All right. I'll narrow my eyes.

139
00:09:28.470 --> 00:09:29.670
That's even worse!

140
00:09:29.740 --> 00:09:31.180
Huh?

141
00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:33.080
Is something wrong?

142
00:09:33.150 --> 00:09:34.140
Uh. no...

143
00:09:35.620 --> 00:09:38.780
It's just that I felt like
I just got a hint.

144
00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:41.920
KONO General Hospital

145
00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:43.680
Boss!

146
00:09:43.760 --> 00:09:46.450
Oh. Umezawa-kun.
Are you alone?

147
00:09:46.530 --> 00:09:48.120
Huh?

148
00:09:48.190 --> 00:09:50.060
What are you hiding for. Ippo?!

149
00:09:50.130 --> 00:09:51.650
Mom!

150
00:09:51.730 --> 00:09:52.700
Go on!

151
00:09:54.270 --> 00:09:57.400
Um. congratulations
on your recovery!

152
00:09:57.470 --> 00:09:59.170
Oh. my.

153
00:09:59.240 --> 00:10:01.710
This is wonderful. but I think
you're making a big deal of it.

154
00:10:01.770 --> 00:10:05.710
That's true. But Umezawa-kun
said I HAD to. so...

155
00:10:05.780 --> 00:10:09.210
This is a day of celebration.
so a bouquet is to be expected!

156
00:10:09.280 --> 00:10:11.080
Do you think so?

157
00:10:11.150 --> 00:10:12.740
More importantly. Boss...

158
00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:14.220
What? Are we going
to bring it out now?

159
00:10:15.790 --> 00:10:18.780
Well. you see. I had a lot of time
on my hands while I was here. so...

160
00:10:20.030 --> 00:10:21.220
Here you are.

161
00:10:21.290 --> 00:10:24.490
Wow. trunks!
Did you make these for me?!

162
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:26.120
What do you think?

163
00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:27.860
They're way better than
your old ones. don't you think?

164
00:10:27.930 --> 00:10:29.300
I'm responsible for the design.

165
00:10:29.370 --> 00:10:31.100
Thanks! They're so cool!

166
00:10:32.040 --> 00:10:33.440
Fishing Boat Rental MAKUNOUCHI

167
00:10:34.210 --> 00:10:35.700
The name of the store's on them!

168
00:10:35.780 --> 00:10:38.470
That's right! You are
a fighting advertisement!

169
00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:39.670
What?!

170
00:10:39.750 --> 00:10:42.910
Don't you dare fall. That wouldn't
be good PR for the store.

171
00:10:42.980 --> 00:10:43.950
You're kidding.

172
00:10:44.020 --> 00:10:46.920
And this is from me.

173
00:10:54.860 --> 00:10:57.260
Are you sure?
Shoes are so expensive.

174
00:10:57.330 --> 00:11:00.230
Let me do this much.
Right?

175
00:11:06.770 --> 00:11:08.240
Thank you both.

176
00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:13.010
I can't return the favor. but I'll
do my best in the upcoming match.

177
00:11:13.080 --> 00:11:15.510
What do you mean?
At least promise us a KO!

178
00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:19.880
<i><font color="#ffff00">They're probably
worried about me...</font></i>

179
00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:21.980
<i><font color="#ffff00">because I haven't
trained enough.</font></i>

180
00:11:23.290 --> 00:11:26.260
<i><font color="#ffff00">I caused everyone a lot of worry
because of what happened.</font></i>

181
00:11:29.060 --> 00:11:30.260
I'll try hard.

182
00:11:31.600 --> 00:11:35.230
I'll give this match my very best.

183
00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:38.530
I can't promise a KO because
Saeki-san is a powerful opponent.

184
00:11:39.540 --> 00:11:41.010
But...

185
00:11:41.940 --> 00:11:43.310
I swear I'll win!

186
00:12:00.560 --> 00:12:01.860
How did it go?

187
00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:03.260
Perfect.

188
00:12:03.330 --> 00:12:05.020
The weigh-in went well. too.

189
00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:07.360
Still. they all look like
they're out for blood.

190
00:12:07.430 --> 00:12:09.490
It means that the fight
is already under way.

191
00:12:09.570 --> 00:12:12.370
Featherweight is next.
Go throw some fear into them...

192
00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:14.100
so they don't
take advantage of you!

193
00:12:15.310 --> 00:12:18.110
A-All right. I'll give it
my full concentration.

194
00:12:19.610 --> 00:12:22.780
<i><font color="#ffff00">That's right.
The fight has already begun.</font></i>

195
00:12:22.850 --> 00:12:24.440
<i><font color="#ffff00">I can't let them
take advantage of me!</font></i>

196
00:12:25.850 --> 00:12:28.720
Oh. it's Makunouchi
who's got eight consecutive KOs.

197
00:12:31.560 --> 00:12:33.550
He's kind of testy. isn't he?

198
00:12:34.460 --> 00:12:36.450
I know you're ready
to take down all comers...

199
00:12:36.530 --> 00:12:39.230
but there's no need to stare down
guys from different weight classes.

200
00:12:41.030 --> 00:12:42.090
Ow.

201
00:12:44.540 --> 00:12:46.060
<i><font color="#ffff00">S- Saeki-san!</font></i>

202
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:47.300
You're Makunouchi-kun!

203
00:12:47.370 --> 00:12:49.030
I'm looking forward to fighting you.

204
00:12:49.110 --> 00:12:51.200
Oh! Ippo's facing down with Saeki!

205
00:12:51.280 --> 00:12:53.770
All right! Give him the evil eye!

206
00:12:56.120 --> 00:12:58.350
P-Pleased to meet you!

207
00:12:59.390 --> 00:13:03.450
Why are you acting shy with the opponent
you're supposed to intimidate?!

208
00:13:03.520 --> 00:13:04.850
Is this it?

209
00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:09.560
So this is the fist that conceals
a wealth of destructive power.

210
00:13:10.400 --> 00:13:11.920
I see.

211
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.260
I heard you were inactive for a while.
but how's your condition?

212
00:13:15.330 --> 00:13:17.030
Don't tell me you injured
your fist or something.

213
00:13:17.100 --> 00:13:19.900
Uh. no. I'm completely fine.
Don't worry.

214
00:13:20.470 --> 00:13:22.440
I see! So you're okay!

215
00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.070
Then hit me with
everything you got.

216
00:13:27.980 --> 00:13:29.210
With everything. okay?

217
00:13:35.390 --> 00:13:37.820
<i><font color="#ffff00">"Hit me with everything you got"?</font></i>

218
00:13:38.960 --> 00:13:41.050
<i><font color="#ffff00">Does that mean
he'll dodge everything?</font></i>

219
00:13:41.830 --> 00:13:45.060
<i><font color="#ffff00">I don't have confidence.
I didn't get enough practice.</font></i>

220
00:13:46.130 --> 00:13:49.930
<i><font color="#ffff00">Will I be able to hit the fastest man
in Featherweight with my punches?</font></i>

221
00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:08.810
He's restless.

222
00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:12.320
Not being able to take part in
training camp is affecting him now.

223
00:14:13.090 --> 00:14:17.050
The kid is the type to gain
confidence from repetitive training.

224
00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:21.290
So he feels pressure
from his lack of training?

225
00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:23.060
Especially because he's up
against a tough customer.

226
00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:27.870
<i><font color="#ffff00">Will I be able to hit him?</font></i>

227
00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:29.810
<i><font color="#ffff00">Will I be able to hit
the Speed Star?</font></i>

228
00:14:31.310 --> 00:14:32.710
Chill out. kid!

229
00:14:32.780 --> 00:14:34.940
Flopping around like
a headless chicken won't help you.

230
00:14:35.780 --> 00:14:37.040
Yes. sir.

231
00:14:37.350 --> 00:14:40.150
<i><font color="#ffff00">He's right. I have
to concentrate and quick.</font></i>

232
00:14:40.220 --> 00:14:42.020
<i><font color="#ffff00">A staffer will call on me
at any minute.</font></i>

233
00:14:44.220 --> 00:14:45.450
Excuse me...

234
00:14:46.030 --> 00:14:47.190
Umezawa-kun!

235
00:14:47.260 --> 00:14:49.520
Whew. that's a relief.
You're in here!

236
00:14:49.930 --> 00:14:52.960
I've never been in a place like this.
you know. It made me nervous.

237
00:14:54.070 --> 00:14:55.690
Thanks for coming!

238
00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:57.360
I invited the boss
to come along...

239
00:14:57.440 --> 00:14:59.230
but she says
she doesn't want to watch.

240
00:14:59.310 --> 00:15:01.000
Huh? Oh.

241
00:15:01.070 --> 00:15:05.670
Anyway. I thought I'd get a picture
of you in all your glory to show her.

242
00:15:05.750 --> 00:15:06.770
Come on. make a pose.

243
00:15:06.850 --> 00:15:08.970
Huh? L-Like this?

244
00:15:09.050 --> 00:15:12.140
Oh. that's good! The trunks
and the shoes look great.

245
00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:15.710
Okay. cheese!

246
00:15:18.160 --> 00:15:20.150
What do you have to push
to make it do that?

247
00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:22.420
I'm sorry! Hold on.
I'll put in a new roll!

248
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:26.190
Makunouchi.
please enter the stadium.

249
00:15:26.270 --> 00:15:27.820
We're going. kid.

250
00:15:27.900 --> 00:15:29.090
Right!

251
00:15:29.440 --> 00:15:30.630
I'm sorry!

252
00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.430
I didn't mean to get you flustered
when you were concentrating.

253
00:15:33.510 --> 00:15:35.800
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

254
00:15:36.880 --> 00:15:40.780
Watch me. Umezawa-kun.
I'll keep my word!

255
00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:46.380
Umezawa. if that's your name.
I'm grateful for your help.

256
00:15:47.950 --> 00:15:49.780
P- Pardon?

257
00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:58.050
Go for it. Saeki-sempai!

258
00:15:58.130 --> 00:16:00.000
Makunouchi's nothing to fear!

259
00:16:02.130 --> 00:16:03.930
We've been waiting for this!

260
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:06.060
Makunouchi.
make it another KO!

261
00:16:06.140 --> 00:16:08.940
Sempai is really popular.

262
00:16:09.010 --> 00:16:11.600
Well. it's due to the reversal KOs
every single time.

263
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:14.770
I believe they're moved by
the struggle of the little guy.

264
00:16:17.550 --> 00:16:19.310
They sure are whooping it up.

265
00:16:19.390 --> 00:16:21.850
I guess that's to be expected
of the most anticipated match.

266
00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:23.950
Are you here on reconnaissance?
That's petty. old guy!

267
00:16:24.020 --> 00:16:28.080
Don't say that. Newbies have
been awfully tough of late.

268
00:16:28.160 --> 00:16:30.690
So. who do you think
will come out on top?

269
00:16:31.060 --> 00:16:33.190
Let me think.

270
00:16:35.330 --> 00:16:36.530
Beats me!

271
00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:39.690
However.
they all have a chance.

272
00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:42.900
Technique. speed.
destructive power.

273
00:16:42.980 --> 00:16:45.540
All of them are excellent
in each category.

274
00:16:45.610 --> 00:16:47.910
For now. I'll enjoy the show.

275
00:16:47.980 --> 00:16:50.740
This match featuring the man with
the strongest fists in Featherweight...

276
00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.980
versus the fastest man
will be something to see.

277
00:16:53.820 --> 00:16:55.180
You got it. don't you?

278
00:16:55.250 --> 00:16:58.120
Overpower Saeki's moves
with right body blows.

279
00:16:59.090 --> 00:17:01.490
What about your plan
to use footwork?

280
00:17:01.560 --> 00:17:04.030
Want to test it out?

281
00:17:04.100 --> 00:17:05.530
I won't use footwork.

282
00:17:05.600 --> 00:17:07.070
The match is six rounds.

283
00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:09.500
I can't possibly catch him
with my footwork.

284
00:17:09.570 --> 00:17:11.370
If I can't follow him.
I'll wait for him!

285
00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:15.870
Your aim is good. However.
if you mess up the timing...

286
00:17:15.940 --> 00:17:18.030
he'll make you into a sandbag
right where you stand.

287
00:17:19.610 --> 00:17:21.480
I'll give it everything I've got!

288
00:17:27.350 --> 00:17:29.340
<i><font color="#ffff00">He's different from the guy
I met at the weigh-in.</font></i>

289
00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:32.610
<i><font color="#ffff00">So he's switched over
from nice guy to bad fighter.</font></i>

290
00:17:33.290 --> 00:17:34.920
<i><font color="#ffff00">Looks like I won't be bored.</font></i>

291
00:17:36.060 --> 00:17:37.120
Seconds out!

292
00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:40.430
Now. this is
the much anticipated match!

293
00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:42.990
Will it go to Makunouchi with his power
or to Saeki with his speed?!

294
00:17:43.070 --> 00:17:44.560
The bell is about to ring!

295
00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:46.830
Hey. you! Sound out!

296
00:17:46.910 --> 00:17:50.360
Go. go. Saeki! Go. go. Saeki!

297
00:17:51.280 --> 00:17:52.640
It's gonna start.

298
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:59.120
Now the bell has rung
to enormous cheers!

299
00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:04.210
<i><font color="#ffff00">Now. let's have a gander at
the power punch you're so proud of!</font></i>

300
00:18:05.760 --> 00:18:07.450
Saeki begins by
establishing a distance.

301
00:18:10.600 --> 00:18:12.930
Makunouchi... doesn't move!

302
00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:15.300
Makunouchi keeps a firm guard
and observes his opponent.

303
00:18:20.510 --> 00:18:23.240
Saeki makes a lap around the ring
centered on Makunouchi.

304
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:25.610
But Makunouchi doesn't move!

305
00:18:25.680 --> 00:18:28.080
<i><font color="#ffff00">What's the matter?
Aren't you gonna try to hit me?</font></i>

306
00:18:28.780 --> 00:18:31.050
<i><font color="#ffff00">The hint is my training
with Yamada-kun.</font></i>

307
00:18:31.780 --> 00:18:33.810
<i><font color="#ffff00">It's difficult to work when
someone's glaring at you.</font></i>

308
00:18:33.890 --> 00:18:36.010
<i><font color="#ffff00">I know it's simple.
but I can put it to practical use!</font></i>

309
00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:40.680
<i><font color="#ffff00">Stare at Saeki-san's
every slightest move!</font></i>

310
00:18:48.200 --> 00:18:51.070
Saeki looks like
he's having a hard time of it.

311
00:18:51.140 --> 00:18:53.660
That's because. to him. it feels
more like he's being waited for...

312
00:18:53.740 --> 00:18:55.500
instead of being watched.

313
00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:57.600
It's a simple strategy.
but it's effective!

314
00:19:00.310 --> 00:19:02.010
What are you doing?
Exchange blows!

315
00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:02.980
Box!

316
00:19:05.220 --> 00:19:07.780
<i><font color="#ffff00">I can't be the first to make
a move. I must wait.</font></i>

317
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.250
What's the matter?!

318
00:19:10.320 --> 00:19:11.980
We didn't come here
to see a staring match!

319
00:19:12.060 --> 00:19:13.820
Saeki! Your opponent's
got the jitters!

320
00:19:14.630 --> 00:19:16.650
<i><font color="#ffff00">He does not. I assure you.</font></i>

321
00:19:16.730 --> 00:19:18.530
<i><font color="#ffff00">If I go near him.
he'll try to bite me.</font></i>

322
00:19:20.400 --> 00:19:23.330
<i><font color="#ffff00">But will he actually
get his teeth in me?</font></i>

323
00:19:33.650 --> 00:19:36.480
Whoops. Saeki casually
strides forward.

324
00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:37.570
What is this?

325
00:19:38.920 --> 00:19:41.010
This pose says "Fight me!"

326
00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:43.350
He is clearly trying
to goad Makunouchi!

327
00:19:45.760 --> 00:19:47.020
And he goes closer...

328
00:19:48.330 --> 00:19:50.490
Makunouchi. one-twos!
He lashes out more!

329
00:19:50.730 --> 00:19:52.030
Saeki only defends!

330
00:19:55.700 --> 00:19:57.860
Saeki takes a powerful
body blow with his guard...

331
00:19:57.940 --> 00:19:59.560
and is blown backwards!

332
00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:02.110
<i><font color="#ffff00">Even the Cross Arm block
doesn't absorb the impact.</font></i>

333
00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:04.770
<i><font color="#ffff00">He's good.</font></i>

334
00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:09.580
Once again
Saeki establishes a distance.

335
00:20:09.650 --> 00:20:12.410
Whew. that was freaky.

336
00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:15.480
He likes to get up close
on purpose to taste the thrill.

337
00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:18.550
That's how Saeki likes
to raise the tension.

338
00:20:19.560 --> 00:20:21.490
He pushes himself to the brink...

339
00:20:21.560 --> 00:20:24.860
to raise his concentration
to the max.

340
00:20:24.930 --> 00:20:28.730
And then.
he'll gear up one by one.

341
00:20:30.600 --> 00:20:33.330
<i><font color="#ffff00">He brought out the rhythm.
He's coming.</font></i>

342
00:20:37.140 --> 00:20:38.470
<i><font color="#ffff00">H- He's fast!</font></i>

343
00:20:42.950 --> 00:20:45.250
<i><font color="#ffff00">He's coming to punch.
Now's my chance!</font></i>

344
00:20:55.230 --> 00:20:56.630
He's fast! He's fast!

345
00:20:56.700 --> 00:20:59.760
Saeki's speed causes Makunouchi's
punches to swing into thin air!

346
00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:02.200
The Speed Star
demonstrates his specialty!

347
00:21:03.570 --> 00:21:05.470
<i><font color="#ffff00">I'm getting shivers.</font></i>

348
00:21:05.540 --> 00:21:07.940
<i><font color="#ffff00">This is it! I can't get enough
of this feeling.</font></i>

349
00:21:08.810 --> 00:21:12.110
<i><font color="#ffff00">It's like Saeki-san is barely
dodging on purpose.</font></i>

350
00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:13.770
<i><font color="#ffff00">But next time...</font></i>

351
00:21:14.110 --> 00:21:15.240
He's good.

352
00:21:15.980 --> 00:21:17.540
Take a good look
at Saeki's position.

353
00:21:20.590 --> 00:21:23.080
He can't catch him by himself...

354
00:21:23.160 --> 00:21:25.450
so he's getting help from the corner.
He's really using his head.

355
00:21:25.520 --> 00:21:26.820
Yes.

356
00:21:29.230 --> 00:21:30.490
<i><font color="#ffff00">He's really something.</font></i>

357
00:21:31.660 --> 00:21:33.390
Now Makunouchi's moving!

358
00:21:33.770 --> 00:21:34.990
A left barrage!

359
00:21:35.070 --> 00:21:38.300
However. Saeki dodges!
Dodges! Dodges and dodges!

360
00:21:50.520 --> 00:21:51.640
<i><font color="#ffff00">That can't be!</font></i>

361
00:21:51.720 --> 00:21:55.480
Oh. my! Saeki escapes
from the corner!

362
00:21:55.550 --> 00:21:58.050
He doesn't allow Makunouchi's fierce
attack to make a single clean hit!

363
00:21:58.120 --> 00:22:00.610
He is definitely a Speed Star!

364
00:22:01.690 --> 00:22:03.660
<i><font color="#ffff00">Thanks.
That had its share of thrills.</font></i>

365
00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:07.020
<i><font color="#ffff00">That's... ridiculous!</font></i>

366
00:23:23.540 --> 00:23:25.480
Clever boxer.

367
00:23:25.540 --> 00:23:29.240
A boxer who fights calmly using
advanced techniques and his brain.

368
00:23:30.020 --> 00:23:31.980
He will monitor
not only his opponent...

369
00:23:32.050 --> 00:23:34.640
but his own condition
objectively throughout a match.

370
00:23:35.350 --> 00:23:38.380
Just when you think you've caught up.
he'll go one level higher.

371
00:23:39.630 --> 00:23:41.720
I still don't want to give up!

372
00:23:41.790 --> 00:23:45.520
I still haven't shown everyone
I made trouble for that I'm okay!

372
00:23:46.305 --> 00:24:46.528
Do you want subtitles for any video?
